{"title_page": "Boston Society of Film Critics Awards 1995", "text_new": "<div style=\"float: right; font-size: smaller; background-color:#E6E6FA; padding: 12px; margin-left: 5em; margin-bottom: 2em; width: 180px\" align=\"center\">\n\n<big>'''16th BSFC Awards'''</big><br />\n<div style=\"padding-left: 15px\">\nDecember 17, 1995\n</div>\n----\nBest Film:<br />\n<big>''' Sense and Sensibility '''</big>\n</div>\nThe '''16th Boston Society of Film Critics Awards''' honored the best filmmaking of [[1995 in film|1995]]. The awards were given on 17 December 1995\n\n==Winners==\n*'''Best Film:'''\n**''[[Sense and Sensibility (film)|Sense and Sensibility]]''\n*'''Best Actor:'''\n** [[Nicolas Cage]] \u2013 ''[[Leaving Las Vegas]]''\n*'''Best Actress:'''\n** [[Nicole Kidman]] \u2013 ''[[To Die For]]''\n*'''Best Supporting Actor:'''\n** [[Kevin Spacey]] \u2013 ''[[The Usual Suspects]]''\n*'''Best Supporting Actress:'''\n** [[Joan Allen]] \u2013 ''[[Nixon (film)|Nixon]]''\n*'''Best Director:'''\n** [[Ang Lee]] \u2013 ''[[Sense and Sensibility (film)|Sense and Sensibility]]''\n*'''Best Screenplay:'''\n**[[Emma Thompson]] \u2013 ''[[Sense and Sensibility (film)|Sense and Sensibility]]''\n*'''Best Cinematography:'''\n**[[Alex Nepomniaschy]] \u2013 ''[[Safe (1995 film)|Safe]]''\n*'''Best Documentary:'''\n**''[[Crumb (film)|Crumb]]''\n*'''Best Foreign-Language Film:'''\n**''[[Mina Tannenbaum]]'' \u2022 [[Netherlands]]/[[France]]/[[Belgium]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.webcitation.org/6C10ZbSA8?url=http://www.thebsfc.org/PastWin.html Past Winners]\n\n==References== \n*[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/boston/access/21424696.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current Hub critics pick `Sense and Sensibility'] ''The Boston Globe''\n*[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000112/1995 1995 Boston Society of Film Critics Awards] ''Internet Movie Database''\n\n{{BSFC Awards Chron}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boston Society Of Film Critics Awards 1995}}\n[[Category:Boston Society of Film Critics Awards|1995]]