6\n|''[[Angel from Hell]]''\n|Linda\n|Recurring role; 5 episodes\n|-\n|2016\u2013present\n|''[[Elena of Avalor]]''\n|Do\u00f1a Paloma\n|Recurring voice role; 10 episodes\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Lopez (TV series)|Lopez]]''\n|Herself\n|Episode: \"George Dates His Daughter\"\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Law & Order True Crime]]''\n|Anthology series; Marta Cano\n|8 episodes\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Undone (TV series)|Undone]]''\n|Camila Diaz\n|Main role; 8 episodes\n|-\n|2019\u2013present\n|''[[Alexa & Katie]]''\n|Dr. Corts\n|Recurring role; 4 episodes\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n* [[Soap Opera Digest Awards]]\n** 1991: Outstanding Female Newcomer (Daytime) \u2013 ''[[Santa Barbara (TV series)|Santa Barbara]]'' (Nominated)\n* [[ALMA Award]]s\n** 1998: Outstanding Actress in a Comedy Series \u2013 ''[[Union Square (TV series)|Union Square]]'' (Nominated)\n** [[9th ALMA Awards|2007]]: Outstanding Actress (Television Series, Mini-Series or Television Movie) \u2013 ''[[George Lopez (TV series)|George Lopez]]'' (Nominated)\n** [[12th ALMA Awards|2011]]: Favorite TV Actress - Supporting Role \u2013 ''[[Switched at Birth (TV series)|Switched at Birth]]'' (Nominated)\n** [[13th ALMA Awards|2012]]: Favorite TV Actress - Supporting Role \u2013 ''Switched at Birth'' ('''Won''')\n* [[Young Artist Award]]s\n** [[25th Young Artist Awards|2004]]: Most Popular Mom & Pop in a Television Series \u2013 ''[[George Lopez (TV series)|George Lopez]]'' (Nominated) with [[George Lopez]]\n* [[Imagen Awards]]\n** 2004: Best Actress in Television Drama \u2013 ''[[American Family (2002 TV series)|American Family]]'' (Nominated)\n** 2004: Best Actress in Television Comedy \u2013 ''George Lopez'' ('''Won''')\n** 2005: Best Actress (Television) \u2013 ''George Lopez'' (Nominated)\n** 2006: Best Actress (Television) \u2013 ''George Lopez'' (Nominated)\n** 2007: Best Actress (Television) \u2013 ''George Lopez'' (Nominated)\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Mexico}}\n* [[List of Mexican Americans]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb name|0005186|Constance Marie}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Marie, Constance}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:American female dancers]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of Mexican descent]]\n[[Category:American soap opera actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Dancers from California]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|American actress of Mexican origin}}\n{{Use American English|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Constance Marie \n| image        = Constance Marie.jpg\n| caption      = Marie at the [[Imagen Awards]] in August 2012\n| birth_name   = Constance Marie Lopez\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1965|9|9}}<ref name=\"TV Guide\">{{cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/constance-marie/bio/145401/|title=Constance Marie Biography, Celebrity Facts and Awards|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=January 23, 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[East Los Angeles, California]], U.S.\n| occupation   = Actress\n| nationality  = American\n| years_active = 1982\u2013present\n| children     = 1\n| website      = {{URL|http://constancemarie.net/|ConstanceMarie.net}}\n}}\n\n'''Constance Marie Lopez''' (born September 9, 1965)<ref name=\"TV Guide\"/> is an American actress of Mexican origin. She is known for her role as Angie Lopez in ''[[George Lopez (TV series)|George Lopez]]'' (2002\u20132007) and her role as Marcela Quintanilla (mother of [[Selena]]) in the film ''[[Selena (film)|Selena]]'' (1997). She portrayed Regina Vasquez in the [[Freeform (TV channel)|ABC Family/Freeform]] drama series ''[[Switched at Birth (TV series)|Switched at Birth]]'' (2011\u20132017). She is currently portraying Camila Diaz in the [[Prime Video]] drama series ''[[Undone (TV series)|Undone]]'' (2019\u2013present).\n\n==Early life==\nAt age 19, Marie appeared as a dancer in the musical ''Cosmopolis'' by composer [[Ryuichi Sakamoto]] in [[Japan]]. When she returned to [[Los Angeles]], she was spotted at a club by a dance choreographer for [[David Bowie]] and she was hired for the [[Glass Spider Tour]] in 1987.\n\n==Career==\nMarie began her acting career when she was in her teenage years. She landed a spot in the 1988 film ''[[Salsa (1988 film)|Salsa]]''. Other television and film credits include ''[[Early Edition]]'', ''[[Dirty Dancing (1988 TV series)|Dirty Dancing]]'', ''[[Selena (film)|Selena]]'', ''[[Spin City]]'', and ''[[Ally McBeal]]''. Marie was chosen for the role of Angie Lopez in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] comedy series ''[[George Lopez (TV series)|George Lopez]]''. In 2001, Marie starred in the comedy-drama film ''[[Tortilla Soup]]'' alongside [[H\u00e9ctor Elizondo]], [[Jacqueline Obradors]], and [[Elizabeth Pe\u00f1a]]. She also appeared in the [[PBS]] drama series ''[[American Family (2002 TV series)|American Family]]''.\n\nIn October 2007, she launched her own clothing line, \"The Constance Marie Collection\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/constance-marie/bio/145401/|title=Constance Marie Biography|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=January 6, 2019}}</ref> In the same year, she appeared in an ad for [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]], encouraging people to spay and neuter their pets.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/stars-support-petas-spay-day/10/|title=Constance Marie|work=[[CBS News]]|accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2011 to 2017, Marie had a starring role in the ABC Family/Freeform drama series ''[[Switched at Birth (TV series)|Switched at Birth]]'', portraying as Regina Vasquez, the birth mother of one of the girls and legal mother of the other.\n\n==Personal life==\nMarie was in a 15-year relationship with yoga instructor Kent Katich, which ended in September 2015.<ref name=\"Separated\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3219890/Constance-Marie-separates-fianc-15-years-Kent-Katich.html|title=Switched At Birth star Constance Marie separates from her fianc\u00e9 of 15 years Kent Katich|last=Pearson|first=Jennifer|work=[[Daily Mail]]|date=September 2, 2015|accessdate=January 31, 2019}}</ref> They have a daughter, Luna Marie, born in February 2009.<ref name=\"Separated\"/> Marie is a longtime [[Vegetarianism|vegetarian]] and raised her child as a vegetarian.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://constancemarie.net/2010/no-moo-for-me-and-luna-marie|title=No \"MOO\" for Me and Luna Marie|last=Marie|first=Constance|work=ConstanceMarie.net|date=August 11, 2010|accessdate=March 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n[[Image:Constance Marie with ALMA.jpg|thumb|right|Marie kissing her trophy at the [[13th ALMA Awards]] in September 2012]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Film\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1988\n|''[[Glass Spider]]''\n|Featured Dancer\n|\n|-\n|''[[Salsa (1988 film)|Salsa]]''\n|Featured Dancer\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[My Family (film)|My Family]]''\n|Toni\n|\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Selena (film)|Selena]]''\n|Marcela Quintanilla\n|\n|-\n|1999\n|''{{sortname|The|Last Marshal|nolink=1}}''\n|Rosa\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Dancing in September]]''\n|Teresa Lopez\n|Television film ([[HBO]])\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2001\n|''[[See Spot Run]]''\n|The Neighbor\n|Uncredited\n|-\n|''[[Tortilla Soup]]''\n|Yolanda\n|\n|-\n|2006\n|''[[Puff, Puff, Pass]]''\n|Montana\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Puss in Boots (2011 film)|Puss in Boots]]''\n|Imelda\n|Voice role\n|-\n|2014\n|''Sweet Surrender''\n|Sandra\n|\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Television\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1988\u20131989\n|''[[Dirty Dancing (1988 TV series)|Dirty Dancing]]''\n|Penny Rivera\n|11 episodes\n|-\n|1989\u20131990\n|''[[Santa Barbara (TV series)|S